\b Making the menu screens\b0 :\par
\par
1) Select Expansion Pack\par
2) Select a Save File\par
3) Game Select\par
4) Puzzle Select\par
5) Options\par
\par
The background is drawn using a repeated 100x100 tile (currently there's a separate bit of placeholder art for each screen; menut1, menut2, menut3, menubt, menubt). This tile should first be used to fill in the whole screen.\par
\par
The banner (the backing for the screen's name) is then drawn in using a 100x80 graphic (called menub1, menub2, menub3, menub4, menub5). This is drawn eight times starting at 0,14, at x+100 intervals.\par
\par
The screen's name, a 400x56 graphic (menun1, menun2, menun3, menun4, menun5) is then drawn at 199,31.\par
\par
These three files ^^^, take up 26K when zipped.\par
\par
The Back button (btext03) is a constant feature of these screens, placed at 27,540.\par
